                        <h1>Speaker Services</h1>                                  
                        Consumer technology professionals from 140 countries come to the International CES to engage with its full lineup of expert speakers and panelists. Share your knowledge and gain critical name recognition as a CES speaker or panelist.<BR><BR>Official International CES speakers receive automatic registration, access to Internet-enabled computers and the opportunity to help shape the consumer technology industry.<BR><BR>If you are speaking at the 2009 International CES, <A href="/print/faq/speakerFAQs.asp">read through the Speaker FAQs</A> to get your questions answered.

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="1842"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Speaker registration and badge pick-up</div>
<br />
As a speaker, you will be registered for the International CES automatically. Upon your arrival, please pick up your badge in the Speaker Ready Rooms: <BR><BR>
<UL>
<LI>LVCC North Hall N263 </LI>
<LI>LVCC South Hall S117 </LI>
<LI>The Venetian, Lando 4301<BR></LI></UL>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="1843"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">On-site Speaker Ready Rooms</div>
<br />
CES speakers have access to our Speaker Ready Rooms. Take advantage of this area to orient yourself with the program location, fine tune your presentation and network with your peers. The Speaker Ready Rooms are located in the Las Vegas Convention Center above the North Hall exhibits next to Room N263 and in the South Hall Room S117/118. The Speaker Ready Room in The Venetian is Lando 4301.<BR><BR>Amenities include:
<UL>
<LI>Speaker work area </LI>
<LI>Computers and Internet access </LI>
<LI>Phones/fax machine </LI>
<LI>Show directories and events schedules </LI>
<LI>Copier </LI>
<LI>Beverage service </LI></UL>Morning and afternoon snacks served each show day on a first-come, first-served basis.

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="1844"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Conference Session Equipment</div>
<br />
The standard A/V available for each conference session includes: 
<UL>
<LI>LCD data projector </LI>
<LI>Podium and podium microphone </LI>
<LI>Shared microphones for panelists </LI>
<LI>8' x 8' screen (or larger) </LI>
<LI>VGA switch box </LI></UL>
<H4>Presentation materials</H4>Speakers who wish to use visuals during their conference session must provide their own laptops and are encouraged to use the International CES PowerPoint template available for download from this page by mid-November.

